# FR-004 — Manage Shapes

**Document ID:** FR-004  
**Status:** Draft  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** 2026-07-16  
**Owner:** Analysis Domain

---

## Purpose

Users shall be able to create, configure, validate, version, inspect and manage spatial Shapes.

A Shape defines a reusable spatial selection rule that can be placed on a Layout and used within an Experiment.

Shapes describe spatial structure. They do not contain draw data, metrics or predictions.

---

## Actors

- Explorer
- Analyst
- Researcher
- Administrator

---

## Functional Requirements

### FR-004.001 — Browse Shapes

The system shall allow users to browse all Shapes they are authorized to access.

Shapes may be filtered by:

- Shape type
- Owner
- Visibility
- Publication status
- Position count
- Compatibility
- Tags

---

### FR-004.002 — View Shape

The system shall display:

- Shape name
- Shape type
- Definition type
- Version
- Owner
- Visibility
- Position count
- Parameters
- Status
- Source or parent Shape, if applicable

---

### FR-004.003 — Create Shape

Authorized users shall be able to create a Shape.

Required information:

- Name
- Shape type
- Definition type
- Visibility

Optional information:

- Description
- Tags
- Anchor definition
- Parameters
- Default weights

---

### FR-004.004 — Define Shape Structure

A Shape may be defined through one of the following methods:

- Relative coordinates
- Geometric parameters
- Logical selection rules
- Manual position selection
- Composite definition

The stored definition must be deterministic and reproducible.

---

### FR-004.005 — Built-in Shape Types

The MVP shall support:

- Single Cell
- Line
- Rectangle
- Square
- Triangle
- Circle
- Ring
- Cross
- L-Shape
- X-Shape
- Custom Selection

---

### FR-004.006 — Configure Parameters

Users shall be able to configure Shape-specific parameters.

Examples:

- Width
- Height
- Radius
- Thickness
- Orientation
- Position count
- Relative weights

Parameter definitions must be validated against the selected Shape type.

---

### FR-004.007 — Validate Shape

Before publication, the system shall validate that:

- the definition is complete,
- the Shape contains at least one selectable position,
- all required parameters are valid,
- no duplicate relative positions exist,
- weights are valid,
- the definition can be resolved deterministically,
- the Shape is compatible with at least one supported Layout.

---

### FR-004.008 — Preview Shape

The system shall provide a visual preview of the Shape.

The preview shall show:

- selected relative positions,
- anchor point,
- dimensions,
- orientation,
- weights, if present,
- invalid or unresolved positions.

The preview may use a neutral reference grid when no Layout is selected.

---

### FR-004.009 — Test Shape on Layout

Users shall be able to place a Shape temporarily on a compatible Layout for validation and preview.

This action shall not create an Experiment.

The system shall indicate:

- valid placements,
- invalid placements,
- boundary conflicts,
- selected Layout positions,
- mapped values.

---

### FR-004.010 — Version Shape

A change affecting Shape structure or analytical behavior shall create a new `ShapeVersion`.

Examples requiring a new version:

- changed coordinates,
- changed dimensions,
- changed geometric parameters,
- changed weights,
- changed anchor behavior,
- changed logical selection rules.

Published Shape Versions are immutable.

---

### FR-004.011 — Edit Metadata

Users may edit non-analytical metadata without creating a new Shape Version.

Examples:

- Display name
- Description
- Tags

Changes affecting analytical behavior require a new version.

---

### FR-004.012 — Duplicate Shape

Users shall be able to create an editable copy of an existing Shape or Shape Version.

The copy shall reference:

- source Shape,
- source version,
- copying user,
- creation timestamp.

---

### FR-004.013 — Fork Published Shape

Authorized users shall be able to fork a published Shape.

The fork shall preserve its relationship to the original publication while remaining independently versioned.

---

### FR-004.014 — Publish Shape

Authorized users shall be able to publish a validated Shape Version.

Published Shape Versions may be:

- used in Experiments,
- shared with other users,
- forked,
- referenced by Studies,
- reviewed by the Community.

---

### FR-004.015 — Archive Shape

Users shall be able to archive a Shape.

Archived Shapes remain available to existing:

- Experiment Versions,
- Experiment Runs,
- Results,
- Publications.

---

### FR-004.016 — Visibility

Shapes shall support:

- private
- workspace
- community
- public
- system

---

### FR-004.017 — Ownership

Every user-created Shape shall record its owner through `created_by`.

---

### FR-004.018 — Shape Compatibility

The system shall determine whether a Shape can be resolved on a selected Layout.

Compatibility may depend on:

- coordinate system,
- available dimensions,
- placement boundaries,
- anchor support,
- Shape definition type.

Compatibility does not imply that every placement is valid.

---

### FR-004.019 — Shape Transformations

The system shall support runtime transformations where compatible:

- Rotation
- Reflection
- Translation

Transformations used in an Experiment must be stored as part of the Experiment or Placement configuration.

A transformation shall create a new Shape Version only when it changes the reusable Shape definition itself.

---

### FR-004.020 — Composite Shapes

The system should support Shapes composed of multiple Shape definitions.

Composite operations may include:

- Union
- Intersection
- Difference

Composite Shapes are outside the minimum MVP execution scope but the model shall remain extensible for them.

---

### FR-004.021 — Weighted Shapes

A Shape may assign weights to its selected relative positions.

Weights may later be used by compatible Metrics or Hit Rules.

Weights must not alter the original Draw data.

---

### FR-004.022 — Random Shapes

Randomly generated Shapes may be supported in a later version.

A random Shape definition must preserve:

- generation algorithm,
- parameter set,
- random seed,
- generated Shape snapshot.

Random generation without a stored seed is prohibited for reproducible Experiments.

---

## Constraints

- A Shape contains at least one relative position or one resolvable selection rule.
- A reusable Shape should remain independent of a specific Lottery.
- A Shape is not permanently placed on a Layout.
- Placement belongs to an Experiment or Placement configuration.
- Published Shape Versions are immutable.
- Existing Experiments retain references to their original Shape Version.
- A Shape does not contain Draws, Metrics, Results or conclusions.
- A Shape must never imply a prediction.

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- A user can create a rectangular Shape.
- A user can define its width and height.
- The Shape can be previewed on a neutral grid.
- Invalid or duplicate positions are rejected.
- A Shape can be tested against a Layout.
- Invalid boundary placements are reported.
- A valid Shape Version can be published.
- Editing a published Shape definition creates a new version.
- Existing Experiments continue referencing the original version.
- A published Shape can be duplicated or forked.
- Unauthorized users cannot modify private Shapes.
- Runtime rotation can be stored without mutating the Shape Version.

